OL,3,CSchizophrenic man who killed three
OL,4,Cpensioners cannot sue authorities for
OL,5,Cdamages
OL,7,FThe latter three organisations claimed
OL,8,Fthe cases should be thrown out based
OL,9,Fon the "doctrine of illegality",
OL,10,Farguing that Lewis-Ranwell should not
OL,11,Freceive damages for the consequences
OL,12,Fof the killings.
OL,14,FThe High Court and Court of Appeal
OL,15,Fruled in 2022 and 2024, respectively,
OL,16,Fthat the claim could continue, but the
OL,17,Fthree bodies told the UK's highest
OL,18,Fcourt in July that it should not be
OL,19,Fallowed to proceed.
