OL,4,Cpensioners cannot sue authorities for
OL,5,Cdamages
OL,7,FIn a majority ruling in February 2024,
OL,8,Ftwo Court of Appeal judges upheld the
OL,9,FHigh Court's decision that the claims
OL,10,Fcould continue.
OL,12,FLord Justice Underhill, with whom Dame
OL,13,FVictoria Sharp agreed, stated that
OL,14,F"someone who was indeed insane should
OL,15,Fnot be debarred from compensation for
OL,16,Fthe consequences of their doing an
OL,17,Funlawful act which they did not know
OL,18,Fwas wrong and for which they therefore
OL,19,Fhad no moral culpability".
OL,26,@vD@AOU{D@YO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
